<br>
Its very hard to choose for me, everytime I think I have it figured out, I look at another skill and think to myself &quot;that would be nice to have.&quot; I really like the 55 skills more than the 59 ones. Anything innate seems more valuable than something on a timer. As paladins we all know it can be a difficult decision for when to use our timed skill. You only get it once every 72 minutes you do not want to use it when you might not need it, then really need it later.<br>
<br>
55 Skills I think are most worthwhile:<br>
Combat Fury<br>
Combat Agility<br>
Combat Stability<br>
Improved Natural Durability<br>
Natural Healing<br>
Mental Clarity<br>
Healing Gift<br>
Healing Adept<br>
Spell Casting Reinforcement<br>
<br>
59 Skills I would use like<br>
Slay Undead<br>
Physical Enhancement<br>
Body and Mind Rejuvination<br>
2hand bash<br>
<br>
 <p><bold><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=101014">Varner Rapscallion</a> 
<br>Crusader for Brell
<br> Master Brewer, Fletcher, Potter, Baker
</bold>
