I just have to have 2h bash, I missed bashing casters with 2 hand weapons.<br>
<br>
It's all personal preferences what you want to improve your char.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufilandiel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Filandiel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/30/02 3:18:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=91.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I had my doubts.......</span><hr size=1> Gilfalas, Fearless is useless 99% of the time, i know i hardly face any mobs that fear me anymore, and the kunark dragon fears are a joke...Level 60 lets you resist about 80% of the fears anyway...you are much better off going SU3, CH LoH, then Holy Steed...though i am off track a bit, hate saving up points, but i am getting Holy Steed now, tired of being a slow ass pally =p, and besides i am tired of people who keep asking me 'when you getting your horse dude?', soon for crissakes!! hehe<br>
