<br>
If you are not going to tough it out till slay 3, then get horse first, because getting slay 1, then horse, then up to slay 3 is a waste. Get your horse sooner, you will enjoy it for longer time, and slay 1 is just frustrating till you get to slay 3.<br>
<br>
As far as fearless, it used to be fun for some things. I used to be immune to necromancer mez/stun spells (&quot;You have resisted fear2&quot;) and I used to be immune to some silence spells (for example Lady Mir in ntov). <br>
<br>
However, in a recent patch this was nerfed, so even those these spells have a roleplaying like fear cause, and the icon they create is something of fear, etc, I am no longer immune. And yes, I am pretty sure it was changed. I spent nearly the whole fight naked with all my resist buffs clicked off at Mir and resisted every single AoE(you do not get a immune message, it just says you resist), and that is a lure level resist, almost no one resists it. When fighting necro mobs, I never got hit by their fear2 spells for a while, then when I noticed the Mir change (I now get hit like everyone else, most of the time, even with 255 MR), I also started getting hit by necro fear2 (mez).<br>
<br>
Being immune to other fearlike spells was pretty cool and rather fun, if not very useful, but now, just being immune to the type of fear that makes you run? Where is that going to help me? I suppose I am the ideal tank for the Gore manaburn squad, or for doing woushi, if I ever did either of those, but I dont. It also means that I can wail on bards when we naked in arena and they expecting to be able to fearkite, but who cares?<br>
<br>
-Iustus<br>
